try on 1) If you try on a piece of clothing, you put it on to see if it fits you or if it looks nice. [V (not )] Try on clothing and shoes to make sure they fit. [Also V ] 2) usu If you say that a person is trying it on, you mean that they are trying to obtain something or to impress someone, often in a slightly dishonest way and without much hope of success. [BRIT, INFORMAL] [V it ] They're just trying it on - I don't believe they'll go this far. [Also V it with ]
